Anonymous Thu 25 Apr 2019 06:09:25 No.22727615 Report
Quoted By:
>>22719152
Not really. The key difference is that hard SF is about the constraints that come with physics and a limited set of macguffins but also about the weird stuff that that enables in terms of society and character behavior, while space opera is about fundamentally recognizable modern humans with space aesthetics used as a multiplier on drama.

In other words, Star Trek is space opera because the science takes a backseat to the moral conundrum of the week or Tragic Wars But Bigger In Space (that are still fundamentally recognizable as human wars but bigger), while Blade Runner is hard SF because it explores how cloning/android stuff has changed society and how people fit into that.

There's not really a hard line, and some stuff is both space opera and hard SF because it looks at both kinds of theme, like The Expanse or Crest of the Stars.
